title: No Pain, No Gain/Who Gives a Buck?
description: In an effort to become physically fit, Rocko and Heffer join a health club.Rocko joins the millions of cash-poor consumers when he gets a credit card.

title: Leap Frogs/Bedfellows
description: In "Leap Frogs," Mrs. Bighead tries to seduce Rocko. In "Bedfellows," Heffer is kicked out of his parents' house, forcing him to live with Rocko.

title: Jet Scream/Dirty Dog
description: Rocko and Heffer have different experiences while traveling by airplane / Rock decides to give Spunky a bath.

title: Keeping Up with the Bigheads/Skid Marks
description: Rocko and Heffer try to makeover Rocko's house after Ed tries to tip his nephew, a city home inspector in a scheme to get rid of Rocko; After Rocko is pulled over because his gas cap is missing, he has to go back to driving school.

title: Power Trip/To Heck and Back
description: When his boss goes out of town, Rocko is left in charge of the store / Heffer experiences the afterlife

title: The Good, the Bad and the Wallaby/Trash-o-Madness
description: Rocko visits his uncle's cattle ranch where Heffer becomes one of the heard / Rocko tries to get his garbage to the curb in time for the garbage men to take it

title: Spitballs/Popcorn Pandemonium
description: Rocko and Heffer go to a baseball game to catch a foul ball and get an autograph / Rocko and Heffer go to the movies

title: A Sucker for the Suck-O-Matic/Canned
description: Rocko buys a cleaning machine from the television to help him clean his house / After being laid off, Rocko searches for a new job

title: Carnival Knowledge/Sand in Your Navel
description: Rocko and Heffer go to a carnival and learn the secret to winning a carnival game.Rocko and Spunky cool off on a hot summer day by spending a nice relaxing day at the beach.

title: Cabin Fever/Rinse and Spit
description: An avalanche traps Rocko, Heffer and the Bigheads in a cabin / Philburt takes his final exam at dental school, and Rocko is his patient

title: Rocko's Happy Sack/Flu-In-U-Enza
description: Rocko and Spunky run to the local grocery store to take advantage of a big sale. Rocko gets the flu and must get cured before the big wrestling match the next night.

title: Who's for Dinner?/Love Spanked
description: Heffer invites Rocko over for dinner with his parents, and Rocko accidentally reveals a secret / Heffer helps Rocko get into dating

title: Clean Lovin'/Unbalanced Load
description: Spunky falls in love with a dirty mop / Rocko decides it's time to do his laundry

title: I Have No Son!
description: Rocko discovers that the Bigheads have a son, and he sets off to find him and bring him back.

title: Pipe Dreams/Tickled Pinky
description: When Rock's toilet is too clogged to flush, he and Heffer try to fix the problem themselves / Rocko has to have his appendix removed

title: The Lounge Singer/She's the Toad
description: Filburt realizes his dream of becoming a lounge singer / After writing a proposal for her sick husband's presentation, Mrs. Bighead is hired as an executive at Conglomo-O

title: Down the Hatch/Road Rash
description: Rocko must take Spunky to the vet after he eats a vitamin that can cause pets to explode / Rocko and Heffer go on a road trip to see Flemm Rock

title: Boob Tubed/Commuted Sentence
description: Rocko purchases a big screen television and Heffer loses his brain inside of it / Rocko's car is impounded which causes him to continually be late for work

title: Rocko's Modern Christmas
description: When elves move in across the street, Rocko invites them and all of O-Town to a Christmas party.

title: Hut Sut Raw/Kiss Me, I'm Foreign
description: Rocko, Heffer, and Filburt go camping, but find it less enjoyable than they expected / When Rocko is going to be deported, he marries Filburt in an attempt to stay in the country

title: Cruisin'
description: Rocko and Heffer get stuck on a senior-singles cruise with Grandpa Wolfe which takes them into the Bermuda Triangle

title: Born to Spawn/Uniform Behavior
description: Filburt comes of age and must go to the islands to spawn. He doesn't want to, for fear of growing up. Heffer becomes a security guard and finds it isn't all he expected it to be, in fact, it's quite scary.

title: Hair Licked/Gutter Balls
description: Rocko is getting his picture taken for the O-Town newspaper. Unfortunately, it's a bad hair day.Ed Bighead will do anything to win the championship trophy. He commissions Rocko, Heffer, and Filburt to play against his woman's auxiliary team.

title: Junk Junkies/Day of the Flecko
description: Rocko has to raise money so he has a garage sale. He finds that his old belongings mean more to him than he thought and he can't sell anything. / A pesky bug (the Flecko) tries to keep Rocko awake.

title: Snowballs/Frog's Best Friend
description: Rocko has to deliver comic books over the snowy mountain. Heffer and Rocko decide to spend the extra time (and money) doing a little skiing. / Bev adopts Earl as her pet. Earl acts viciously to Ed but like a pussycat to Bev.

title: Short Story/Eyes Capades
description: Rocko feels very short until he does something very big./Rocko is competing in the Jack Hammer finals, but has a problem with his eyesight.

title: Bye, Bye Birdie/Belch of Destiny
description: Rocko "birdsits" Filburt's problem bird, Tirdy, when Filburt is sick. The bird dies when Heffer sits on it and Rocko and Heffer panic. / Heffer uses his unusual burping talent to secure a place for his troop of Weasel Scouts at Astro Camp.

title: The Emperor's New Joe/Schnit-Heads
description: Rocko falls prey to the Chameleon Brother's latest scam: a trendy new cafe which features a rather interesting brew. / Heffer becomes the newest member of the Sausage Club and it's up to Rocko and Filburt to save him from nitrate-induced hysteria.

title: Sugar-Frosted Frights/Ed Is Dead: A Thriller!
description: Hessian and the potency of candy when Rocko and Heffer introduce him to the concept of trick-or-treating. / Something in a Hitchcock-ian vein: Rocko suspects Bev Bighead of foul play when Ed disappears mysteriously.

title: Fish-N-Chumps/Camera Shy
description: Rocko, Heffer, and Filburt set out for a day of fantastic fishing - but the fish have other plans!/Rocko sets out to make a video tape to send home to his parents.

title: Nothing to Sneeze At/Old Fogey Froggy
description: Bev Bighead mistakenly gets a nose through accidental surgery and enjoys all the new aromas she encounters - all but the smell of her husband Ed./After being passed up for a promotion at work for a younger man, Ed experiences a mid-life crisis.

title: Manic Mechanic/Rocko's Happy Vermin
description: Rocko's car dies, but is recusitated to win the O-Town rally with Heffer piloting the car in reverse./Rocko finds himself in the middle of a plan to get Ed Bighead's private stock of bugs off the menu and into the good life.

title: I See London, I See France/The Fatlands
Fortune Cookie/Dear John
description: Filburt receives a horrible fortune from a Chinese fortune cookie just before he is to enter the Mega Spin./Rocko's kitchen is destroyed by a government satellite right before his big party. He and Heffer attend Home Show conventions.

title: Speaking Terms/Tooth and Nail
description: After a big fight, Rocko and Heffer find themselves guests on "The Nosey Show", a daytime TV talk show./Rocko is forced into a twelve-step self-help program in order to come to grips with his nail-biting problem.

title: Wacky Delly
description: In order to get out of a contract with his network, cartoonist Ralph Bighead hires fans Rocko, Heffer, and Filburt to create a sure-fire failure of a series that, much to his dismay, becomes a success.

title: The Big Question/The Big Answer
description: The moment we've all been waiting for: Filbert overcomes his fear and decides to ask Doctor Hutchison to marry him. /Dr. Hutchinson beats Filbert to the punch and asks him to marry her.

title: An Elk for Heffer/Scrubbin' Down Under
description: In order to officially become an adult member of the Wolf Pack,Heffer must bring home an elk for dinner./Rocko's hygiene is under scrutiny after his "spinach tooth" is revealed nationwide during his accepance speech.

title: Zanzibar!/Fatal Contraption
description: O-Town begins a massive musical recycling campaign. /Rocko purchases a lonely food processor, Food Boy.

title: With Friends Like These/Sailing the Seven Zzzz's
description: Rocko wins two free tickets to a wrestling match from a radio show./Ed Bighead's sleepwalking problem, triggered by the memory of an early childhood trauma, spells high adventure for Rocko and Spunky!

title: Pranksters/From Here to Maternity
description: It's the ultimate April Fools Day in O-Town as Rocko, Filburt, and Heffer try their best practical jokes on one another./Filburt's impending fatherhood is jeopordized by the Easter Bunny's fiendishly clever Lamaze class egg ring.

title: Ed Good, Rocko Bad/Teed Off
description: Rocko is unjustly imprisoned in the O-Town dog pound and incensed by he squalid conditions /When Heffer lands a part time job as an assistant greenskeeper at a prestigious golf course, he finds himself embroiled in Ed Bighead's office politics.

title: Wimp on the Barbie/Yarnbenders
description: Heffer transforms Rocko from milquetoast to Terminator./Classic fairy tales take on a decidedly new twist when Rocko convinces Heffer to read to a sick Filburt from "The Really, Really Big Book of Fairy Tales."

title: Mama's Boy/Feisty Geist
description: After suffering some ribbing from Rocko and Filburt, Heffer decides to move out of his parents home and strike out on his own./Rocko and Heffer's visit to a fortune teller channels them into danger when the spirit of Mortimer Khan possesses Spunky.

title: S.W.A.K./Magic Meatball
description: Rocko falls for Alicia, his new mail carrier, but his plan to give her a love letter goes awry when Heffer takes over her route while she's sick./Ed Bighead is promoted to an executive at Conglomo.

title: Closet Clown/Seat to Stardom
description: When a clown's truck breaks down in front of his house, Ed Bighead begins to lead a double life./Rocko's behind earns him a place among the beautiful people of the fashion world when he becomes the spokes-wallaby for "Wedgie Boy" undergarments.

title: The High-Five of Doom/Fly Burgers
description: After stumbling upon Filburt's secret diary, Heffer and Rocko are convinced that Filburt is an alien./Flecko the fly files a lawsuit against Rocko after tripping on a rock in his house.

title: Heff in a Handbasket/Wallaby on Wheels
description: Heffer finds himself in the midst of a Faustian bargain when he offers his soul to a devil named Peaches so that he can compete on a television trivia show with fabulous prizes.

title: Dumbells/Rug Birds
description: Heffer and Filburt introduce Rocko to the all-American pastime of "Ding-Dong-Ditch."/Filburt, the obsessive collector of bird wigs, takes Rocko along for his biggest score: the wig of an American Balding Eagle!

title: Hypno-Puppy Luv/Driving Mrs. Wolfe
description: Heffer and Filburt hypnotize Rocko into thinking he's a dog./Rocko, after unwittingly being recruited as Mrs. Wolfe's driving instructor, finds himself riding shotgun in a deadly game of chicken against the ultimate demolition derby car.

title: Put to Pasture/Future Schlock
description: Heffer overdoses on Pasture Puffies and is rushed to the hospital./In the O-Town of the far-flung future, Gilbert and Norbert -- descendants of a now ancient Filburt -- discover the remains of an old banana.

title: Turkey Time/Floundering Fathers
description: The special plans for Rocko's first Thanksgiving go awry when the turkey's of O-Town escape and take refuge in Rocko's house./The residents of O-Town engage in an argument about the correct origin of the town.
